  "body": "## Preamble\r\n\r\n    VIP: <to be assigned>\r\n    Title: Standardize type conversions\r\n    Author: David Knott\r\n    Type: Standard Track\r\n    Status: Draft\r\n    Created: 2018-01-11\r\n\r\n\r\n## Simple Summary\r\nRight now Vyper type conversions are not uniform, they are performed by built in functions with different syntax:\r\n`decimal` \r\n`bytes_to_num`\r\n`as_num128` (int128\r\n`as_num256` (uint256)\r\n\r\n\r\n## Abstract\r\nI propose standardizing how type conversions are performed in Viper.\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nStandardizing type conversion will simplify both the developer experience and the compiler by  decreasing the amount of build in functions.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n```\r\nconvert(input, new_typ)\r\ndecimal => convert(1, decimal) => 1.0\r\nbytes_to_num =? convert('\\x00', num) => 0\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nThis change won't be backwards compatible, if it's implemented it should be done in the next release.\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)",
